---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - NoteGuard">
    <main class="pt-20 pb-20">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
            <div class="mb-12">
                <a
                    href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`}
                    class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-2 mb-6"
                >
                    ‚Üê Back to Home
                </a>
                <h1
                    class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-pink-600 mb-4"
                >
                    Privacy Policy
                </h1>
                <p class="text-gray-400">Last updated: December 16, 2025</p>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-300">
                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        Introduction
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        NoteGuard ("we," "our," or "us") is dedicated to
                        protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines
                        how your information is handled when you use the
                        NoteGuard mobile application.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong
                            >Our core philosophy is simple: Your data belongs to
                            you.</strong
                        > NoteGuard is designed as an offline-first application with
                        on-device AI processing. We do not collect, store, or transmit
                        your personal notes or audio recordings to any cloud servers.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        Data Collection and Usage
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        We do not collect any personal data. All data created
                        within the app remains stored locally on your device.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Notes and Content:</strong> Texts, images, and
                            other content you create are stored in your device's internal
                            storage and are encrypted where applicable.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Audio Recordings:</strong> Voice notes are processed
                            locally using on-device AI models (like Whisper) and are
                            never uploaded for transcription.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>AI Processing:</strong> All AI features, including
                            summarization and chat, run entirely on your device using
                            local LLMs. No data is sent to external APIs (like OpenAI
                            or Gemini) unless you explicitly configure a third-party
                            extension (if available in future updates).
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        App Permissions
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        NoteGuard requires certain permissions to function
                        correctly:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Microphone:</strong> Required solely to record
                            audio for voice notes and transcription. Audio data is
                            processed in real-time on your device.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Storage:</strong> Required to save your notes
                            and backups to your device.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Biometrics:</strong> Required if you choose to
                            lock your notes or the app. Biometric authentication is
                            handled by the Android system; we do not store your fingerprint
                            or face data.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        Third-Party Services
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        Since NoteGuard functions offline, we do not integrate
                        with third-party tracking or analytics services that
                        collect usage data.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        Changes to This Policy
                    </h2>
                    <p class="mb-4">
                        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We
                        will notify you of any changes by posting the new
                        Privacy Policy on this page.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">
                        Contact Us
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy,
                        please contact us via our GitHub repository issues page.
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
</Layout>
